<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1550 GMT, September 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Sam Rainsy, the main opposition leader left the
Cambodiana Hotel where he took refuge while protests against the
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen continued on Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Sam Rainsy left the hotel under the protection of UN officials
at about 10:30 am local time, and went straight to another
opposition leader, Prince Ranariddh's residence. (Cambodia-Sam
Rainsy-Protests)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The Real IRA, the terrorist group that bombed Omagh
in Northern Ireland last month, said on Tuesday it was declaring a
"complete" ceasefire starting from Monday midnight.
</P>
<P>
The republican splinter group, which suspended its armed
activities three days after the Omagh blast that killed 29 people
on August 15, issued its ceasefire announcement to Ireland's
national broadcasting network RTE. (Britain-N.Ireland-Ceasefire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian police dispersed with water cannons and
batons thousands of demonstrators protesting outside the National
Assembly (parliament) Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred policemen blocked a park that the demonstrators
called "Democracy Square" and removed tents and makeshift shelters
in the park. (Cambodia-Protest-Dispersal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ULAN BATOR -- The leadership of the Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party (MPRP) said Tuesday that the Great Hural
(parliament) has to be dismissed if it fails to appoint a new
government as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"The government crisis, which was caused by the wrong policy of
the ruling union -- the Mongolian National Democratic Party and
the Mongolian Social Democratic Party, is intensified and those in
power were unable to get the country out of the current political
deadlock, thus leading to a parliament crisis," the MPRP said in a
statement to all people of Mongolia. (Mongolia-Cabinet
Crisis-MPRP)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Central Bank President Sergei Dubinin offered
his resignation Monday and went on leave while his appeal is being
considered, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Dubinin's post now is taken over by Deputy Finance Minister
Sergei Aleksashenko until a new head is appointed. (Russia-Bank
Chief-Resignation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- A southern African summit on the Congolese (K)
conflict ended at Victoria Falls on Tuesday without agreement on a
cease-fire, according to reports from the Zimbabwean town.
</P>
<P>
Seven presidents including three backing Congolese President
Laurent Kabila's government and two opposing it gathered for a
second round of talks Tuesday, promising an immediate end to the
fighting. (Congo (K)-Regional Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A Palestinian diplomat said on Tuesday that Israel has
launched an anti-Egypt campaign with ulterior motives, Egypt's
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Ambassador in Cairo Zohdi al Kodra shrugged off as
"tendentious and suspicious" Israel's allegations that Egypt
pressured Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat during his recent visit
to Cairo to reject any agreement with Israel on the further
withdrawal from the West Bank, the news agency said.
(Egypt-Israel-Palestinians) 
</P>
