<DOCNO> XIE19980909.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Foreign Reserves Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's total
gold and foreign reserves rose 33.8 million Rand (5.5 million
U.S. Dollars) to 32.7 billion Rand (5.3 billion Dollars) in
August, the South African Reserve Bank said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Gold reserves increased by 157.5 million Rand (25.4 million
Dollars) to 6.7 billion Rand (1.1 billion Dollars) at the end of
August, the bank said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
But foreign assets decreased by 123.7 million Rand (20 million
Dollars) to 26 billion Rand (4.2 billion Dollars), it said.
</P>
<P>
There was no change in the government loans and advances at
626.5 million Rand (101 million Dollars), while re-sale
agreements with banks went down 1.4 billion Rand (226 million
Dollars) to 9.8 billion Rand (1.6 billion Dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the liabilities side, the amount of notes and coins in
circulation in South Africa rose 237.9 million Rand (38.4 million
Dollars) to 23.3 billion (3.8 billion Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Government deposits rose 176.3 million Rand (28.4 million
Dollars) to 913.4 million Rand (147.3 million Dollars), while
those for banks fell 545 million Rand (87.9 million Dollars) to
7.5 billion Rand (1.2 billion Dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
