<HEADLINE> Turkey Says Willing to Strengthen Ties with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Parliament Speaker
Hikmet Cetin said here Tuesday that Turkey is willing to promote
cooperation with China in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Cetin made the remark during a meeting with a visiting Chinese
women delegation headed by Li Xiaolin, vice-president of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign
Countries (CPAFFC).
</P>
<P>
Cetin said Turkey always attaches great importance to its
relations with China and is ready to develop economic and trade
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there is great potential in enhancing economic
cooperation between Turkey and China, which should be further
tapped through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish parliament speaker said that the Turco-Chinese
ties should be promoted not only through official contacts of the
two governments, but also through the people-to-people exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiaolin, for her part, said that the Sino-Turkish relations
have been smoothly developing in recent years, laying a solid
foundation for the non-governmental contacts.
</P>
<P>
She said the CPAFFC will work for better understanding and
friendship between the peoples of China and other countries
including Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived here Monday morning for a
goodwill visit to Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
