<HEADLINE> Bus Collision Kills At least 51 in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Two buses collided with a
tanker truck Tuesday in southern Brazil, killing at least 51
people and injuring some 40 others.
</P>
<P>
The buses were carrying about 100 passengers on a religious
pilgrimage when they ran into the truck which had lost control on
a highway in Sao Paulo state, eyewitnesses said.
</P>
<P>
The accident was the worst in Sao Paulo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
