<HEADLINE> Greece, Albania Sign Protocol of Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Albania signed
Tuesday a protocol of cooperation aimed at providing Greek support
to Tirana in its efforts to join European and Atlantic
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The protocol was signed here by Greek Alternate Foreign
Minister George Papandreou and his visiting Albanian counterpart,
Ilir Meta.
</P>
<P>
The two men also discussed the situation in the Yugoslav
province of Kosovo, where ethnic Albanians make up 90 percent of
its nearly two million population and have been seeking
independence from Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that there must be greater activity from the
international community for a political and peaceful solution in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
They agreed on the need for solutions to be found through a
dialogue, peaceful processes to ensure peace and cooperation
between peoples of all the region, Papandreou said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that regional cooperation had great
significance for progress, and the two countries were working
closely in the framework of this cooperation for regional
stability. 
