<HEADLINE> Mozambique Urges More Concerns for Poor States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tomaz Salomao, Planning and Financial Minister, said at the
opening ceremony of symposium on new European currency that
Mozambique is greatly concerned over the new Euro Dollar and the
establishment of Euro Dollar zones and its system, as Europe is
an important trade partner with Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique is one of the poorest countries in the world and
about two thirds of the poorest countries are located in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Salomao said that about 33 percent of Mozambique's export
last year went to European Union countries, and 22 percent of
its import came from Europe.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique exported about 230 million U.S. Dollars worth of
goods last year, and exported products of one billion Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that his country has had a high growth rate
with low inflation in recent years, adding that most of its big
state-run enterprises would go privatized this year.
</P>
<P>
About 400 people attended the one-day symposium on Euro
Dollar. 
</P>
