He noted that Israel's defense spending has shrunk in recent
years amid mounting threat from other countries in the Middle
East, such as Iran and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The radio said that the Israeli cabinet is still holding
marathon talks over the 1999 budget while a majority of ministers
has voiced opposition to Mordechai's proposal.
</P>
<P>
But Finance Ministry sources said that Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu and Finance Minister Ya'acov Neeman, who support the
budget increase, will finally pressure the cabinet to approve the
proposal. 
