<HEADLINE> Fyodorov Outlines Government Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian Acting Vice-Premier
Boris Fyodorov on Tuesday said that the government program to be
passed by the Cabinet is aimed at the resumption of genuine
reforms.
</P>
<P>
In his statement faxed to the Itar-Tass news agency Fyodorov
said that he is surprised that some renown economists, including
Yegor Gaidar, comment on the government program which have not
been seen by them with their eyes.
</P>
<P>
He said the concept of the program does not provide for "money
minting", it aims at the resumption of genuine reforms, which have
been actually stopped in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Fyodorov outlined three sets of measures included in the
program: a tough monetary system; a well-ballanced budget and a
radical tax reform.
</P>
<P>
All that will encourage structural changes in the economy and
raise its efficiency, a policy of raising the labor productivity
and a more rational distribution of resources, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fyodorov meanwhile urged the Central Bank to stop ruble rate
games, and let the national currency to form freely on the market.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank should explain to the population that the
ruble rate is falling due to speculative pressure, with money
supply remaining practically unchanged, he noted.
</P>
<P>
In his view, the Bank should re-evaluate commercial banks'
mandatory reserves for hard-currency deposits at the ruble rate as
was quoted on August 14, 1998, and make them interest-bearing and
dollar-denominated.
</P>
<P>
He also said the state should give an unconditional guarantee
of populations' deposits as of August 14 to an amount of up to
5,000 dollars, using banks' reserves and property for the purpose.
</P>
