<HEADLINE> 52nd Session of General Assembly Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The 52nd session of the
General Assembly concluded here on Tuesday after a year of hard
work and intensive discussions.
</P>
<P>
In the course of the session, the General Assembly considered a
total of 163 items, held 92 plenary meetings and 22 meeting in the
format of open-ended informal consultations of the plenary and
adopted 298 resolutions and 146 decisions.
</P>
<P>
It Adopted the resolutions on the Prohibition of the Use,
Stockpiling, Production ans Transfer of Anti-Personnel mines and
on their Destruction, on supporting the initiative to establish
one more nuclear - free zone in Central Africa, and the
international convention for the Suppression of terrorist
Bombings. 
