<HEADLINE> G7 Meeting on Russia Likely to be Postponed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The British government
announced Tuesday that the scheduled meeting on Russian situation
by the Group of Seven (G7) industrial nations is likely to be
postponed until next Monday.
</P>
<P>
A British government official said Monday that the G7 meeting
would be held on September 12, but a Foreign Office spokesman was
quoted by Reuters as saying early Tuesday the meeting is likely to
be postponed.
</P>
<P>
"It looks like Monday (September 14) is better for most people
but until we have heard from all of our partners we can't confirm
it. It is unlikely we will have that confirmation before tomorrow
(Wednesday)," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from vice ministers from the G7 -- Canada, the United
States, France, Germany, Italy, Britain and Japan, representatives
from the International Monetary Fund, World Bank and the European
Commission are also expected to attend the London talks.
</P>
<P>
The London meeting is expected to take stock of Russia's
deepening financial crisis and make various recommendations to G7
leaders. 
