<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan,
the Regent, reiterated Tuesday that Jordan continues to "exert its
uttermost efforts" to support the Palestinians to establish an
independent state with its capital in Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
All of Jordan's efforts and moves will serve the aim, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hassan made the remarks in meeting with Mahmoud Abbas,
Secretary General of the Executive Committee of the Palestine
Liberation Organization.
</P>
<P>
Abbas, also known as Abu Mazen, is also regarded as the deputy
head of the Palestinian National Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
