<HEADLINE> Visiting Indian President Meets German Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- German President Roman Herzog and
Chancellor Helmut Kohl Tuesday met visiting Indian President
Kocheril Raman Narayanan, both stressing the need for
confidence-building efforts between India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
According to German government spokesman Otto Hauser, the talks
between Kohl and Narayanan focused on bilateral relations, the
situation in South Asia as well as the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Restating Germany's criticism of the nuclear tests conducted by
India and Pakistan earlier this year, Kohl called on both
countries to resume their dialogue and seek confidence-building
measures in order to prevent an arms race.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Kohl also stressed Germany's interest to
continue economic cooperation with Asian countries. He also called
on India to carry on economic reforms and improve the conditions
for German investment.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a banquet honoring his Indian counterpart Tuesday
evening, German President Roman Herzog also voiced criticism of
Indian and Pakistani nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged both countries to overcome their rivalry through
confidence-building policies, just as Germany and France did after
World War II.
</P>
<P>
Narayanan, who is on a four-day visit to Germany, is due to
hold talks with German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel on Wednesday.
</P>
