<HEADLINE> Airbus, Boeing Snatch Big Orders at Farnborough </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Airbus Industrie, the major
European air consortium, and American air giant Boeing have both
won some lucrative orders at the on-going Farnborough
International Air Show.
</P>
<P>
Airbus Industrie, in buoyant form after recently wrestling a
plum British Airways contract from Boeing, Tuesday signed a
contract for six A340-500s with options for a further 10 with
Emirates Airline.
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles-based International Lease Finance Corporation
also agreed to place orders for 16 Airbus aircraft in a deal worth
hundreds of millions of dollars.
</P>
<P>
Although the Airbus chief executive Noel Forgeard declined to
give a precise figure of the deals, the two deals were in total
worth up to 1.6 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Airbus's major global arch-rival Boeing Monday also
unveiled a $900-million order from International Lease Finance
Corp and a $230-million order from the Dutch airline KLM.
</P>
<P>
It is widely expected that Airbus and Boeing would take full
advantage of the Farnborough air show to announce more orders in
the following days, intensifying their the head-to-head dogfight
over global market shares. 
</P>
