<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Restraint by Iran, Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The United States Tuesday
urged Iran and Afghanistan to restrain themselves from taking any
steps in escalating tensions between them.
</P>
<P>
"We are urging restraint by all sides. We want Afghanistan's
neighbors to refrain from taking actions that could further
enlarge or inflame the conflict, and obviously, to respect its
international borders," State Department spokesman James Rubin
said at a regular briefing.
</P>
<P>
