of troops and equipment" on its border with Afghanistan and said
they should be left there following a military exercise.
</P>
<P>
"Clearly, this is a matter of serious concern, and it's
something we're watching extremely closely," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said Washington could not confirm reports that a number
of Iranian diplomats had been missing or killed in an Afghan city
the Taliban recently captured.
</P>
<P>
But while stressing that holding diplomats "for any reason or
at any time" was unacceptable under international law, he made
clear "we do not support any interference in the internal affairs
of Afghanistan." 
