<HEADLINE> Italian Drugs lab Head Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 9 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary Emilio
Gasbarrone of Italy's dope testing laboratory was suspended for
one month on Wednesday in the wake of a scandal over drugs
testing of the country's footballers.
</P>
<P>
The action against Gasbarrone came at an emergency meeting
here of the national Olympic committee (CONI), which governs
sport in Italy and which appointed the laboratory at Acqua
Acetosa near Rome.
</P>
<P>
The scandal broke last weekend when it emerged that Italy's
war on drugs was a sham. Only a fraction of 4,000 samples sent in
and paid for each year by Serie A and B clubs were ever tested
for steroids.
</P>
<P>
The laboratory, though working for the CONI, is run by the
Italian Sports Doctors Federation, of which Professor Giorgio
Santilli is president.
</P>
<P>
The CONI decided that Santilli should explain the goings-on
at Acqua Acetosa and that a CONI national council meeting on
September 17 should make a judgement on CONI's own president
Mario Pescante's actions in the affair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
