<HEADLINE> ASEAN Urges All Parties in Cambodia to Avoid Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 9 (Xinhua) -- In a statement issued
tonight, ASEAN urged all parties in Cambodia to exercise
restraint, avoid violence and resolve their problems through
dialogue and consultations in order to prevent a further
deterioration of the situation.
</P>
<P>
The statement was issued by Chairman of the ASEAN Standing
Committee S Jayakumar, who is Singapore Foreign Minister, after
consulting with the other ASEAN Foreign Ministers, according to a
press release from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The following is the full text of the statement:
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN Statement on Cambodia
</P>
<P>
In view of the increasing tension in Phnom Penh, ASEAN urges
all parties concerned to respect the results of the 26 July 1998
general elections which were generally recognized by the
international community as free and fair, as well as to exercise
restraint, avoid violence, including extremist acts, and resolve
their problems through dialogue and consultations in order to
prevent further deterioration of the situation.
</P>
<P>
In this connection, ASEAN reiterates its call in the ASEAN
Statement on Cambodia on 4 September 1998 on all parties concerned
in Cambodia to resolve their differences in the spirit of national
reconciliation and unity so that a new national assembly could
soon vote on a new government, thus contributing to the peace and
stability in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
It is to be recalled that at the request of the Cambodian
government, ASEAN -- through the ASEAN Troika -- has been engaging
with cooperation and support from the international community, in
efforts to assist in the restoration of political stability in
Cambodia. ASEAN thus hopes that all Cambodian parties will try to
build on the achievements that they themselves have made so far on
the restoration of political normalcy, internal order and the
national reconciliation process, especially after the 26 July 1998
elections.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN strongly supports His Majesty King Sihanouk's role in
solving the present situation so that Cambodia would soon form a
new government that fulfills the aspirations of the Cambodian
people and the desire of the countries in the region."  
</P>
</TEXT>
