occurred in central and northern Greece respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the Athens-Thessaloniki national highway just several
kilometers outside the central Greek town of Larissa, a passenger
vehicle crashed into a tourist coach heading to the Greek capital
city of Athens from Thessaloniki, killing the driver of the
passenger vehicle, and just after the accident, a small truck ran
into the coach passengers milling about on the highway, killing
another two people and injuring 12, the semi- official Athens News
Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
