<HEADLINE> Beckenbauer Rules himself Out for German Coach Job </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Franz Beckenbauer ruled
himself out for the job of Germany's soccer coach Wednesday and
suggested Holland's Johan Cruyff would be fitting for the post.
</P>
<P>
Berti Vogts resigned as the national team coach Monday after
the side's 3-0 loss to Croatia in the World Cup quarter-finals
and poor performances in last week's two friendlies.
</P>
<P>
Beckenbauer, a former star player who guided Germany to its
third and last World Cup title in 1990, said he had left the
coaching job for good.
</P>
<P>
But he recommended Cruyff, the most venerated Dutch soccer
star who was his greatest rival in 1970s, for the vacant job.
</P>
<P>
Cruyff turned down an offer to become coach of the Dutch
national team last month. 
