<HEADLINE> Double-Tracking Set for Beijing-Kowloon Railway Section </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese railway departments
plan to allocate 200 million yuan this year to double-track the
60-km Dingnan-Longchuan Section along the southern stretch of the
Beijing-Kowloon Railway Line.
</P>
<P>
Construction commenced in August and is scheduled for
completion by the end of this year, said sources from south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The 2,536-km north-south trunk line from Xiangtang, Jiangxi
Province, northwards was double-tracked during initial
construction. Double-tracking projects have not as yet been
carried out on some 273 km in the southern section of the railway
line.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 213-km section of the railway line from Longchuan
to Dongguan will begin to be double-tracked in 1999. 
</P>
