<HEADLINE> Chinese Company to Build Hydropower Station in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Albania's government approved a
contract with a Chinese company Tuesday to build the Bushat
hydropower station.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government believed that the proposal to build the
Bushat hydropower station over the Drin River by Hainan Science,
Technology and Trade Company of China, required the lowest
investment and had the most favorable loan terms.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese company won the contract through a competitive
bidding process, participated in by many international companies,
The Chinese company will provide a line of credit worth 149.66
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The station is located on the reaches lower than the Fjerze
hydropower station, which was also built by a Chinese company. The
Bushat will be another major hydropower station on the river. Two
sets of Chinese generators will be installed with a capacity of
80,000 kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
It will generate 350 million watt/hours of electricity when it
goes into operation and help alleviate the country's power
shortage. 
</P>
