<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Unemployment Rate Unchanged in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union
unemployment rate remained at 10.1 percent in July while the euro
zone jobless rate went slightly down, Eurostat reported on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
communities said that unemployment for the 11-nation single
currency zone was at 11.1 percent in July, compared with 11.2
percent posted a month earlier.
</P>
<P>
The euro zone jobless rate was 11.7 percent in July 1997 while
the figure for the union in the corresponding period was 10.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
At 2.3 percent, Luxembourg still had the lowest unemployment
rate among the 15 EU member states whereas Spain, though
witnessing a 0.2 percentage point drop, had the highest at 18.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
A year earlier, however, Spain had a jobless rate of 21 percent.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat estimated that some 16.9 million men and women were
without a job in July within the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
