<HEADLINE> No More International Club Soccer Games in Stockholm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Stockholm will no longer
host any international club matches because they are costly,
Swedish Football Association president Lars-Ake Lagrell said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Lagrell said they gave it up for they do not have enough
policemen to man the matches.
</P>
<P>
Policing of last May's European Cup Winners' Cup final in
Stockholm in which Chelsea beat VfB Stuttgart 1-0 cost police an
estimated five million Swedish crowns ($631,200), with about
1,000 police on duty.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish F.A. will in future stage international club
matches in Gothenburg on the west coast.
</P>
<P>
However, major internationals, such as last Saturday's
European championship qualifier between Sweden and England, will
still be held in Stockholm. 
</P>
