<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientist Elected Chairman of World Glaciology Organization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Qin Dahe, a well-known Chinese
scientist, was elected chairman of the glaciological research
workshop under the International Science Commission of Antarctic
Research today in this capital of northwest China's Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
The election result was announced at the closing session of the
Sixth International Symposium on Antarctic Glaciology this
afternoon, and Qin became the first Chinese glaciologist to take
the position of chairman in the workshop, which is the world's top
research organization in the field.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists initiated the research on Antarctic glaciers
in the 1980s and have achieved scientific developments during the
past decade.
</P>
<P>
Qin crossed the Antarctic Continent on foot in 1990 and
conducted abundant research projects, which have played leading
roles in world glaciological research circles.
</P>
<P>
He has gained a great reputation among both Chinese and foreign
experts who agreed that Qin and his laboratory under the Chinese
Academy of Sciences has caught up with their world counterparts.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
