<HEADLINE> HK-based Wen Wei Po Marks 50th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 people from
various circles attended a reception here Wednesday, marking the
50th anniversary of the publishing of Wen Wei Po, a
Chinese-language newspaper in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, Chang Yun-feng, chairman and director
of Wen Wei Po, reviewed the brilliant history of the newspaper's
development over the past half century.
</P>
<P>
He said that the key to the maintenance of the paper's vigor
mostly depends on that "we have always combined ourselves closely
with the destiny of the people of the motherland and the Hong Kong
compatriots who love the country."
</P>
<P>
"All of my colleagues are determined to continuously develop
the strong points and overcome shortcomings so as to greet new
challenges towards the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper office has received congratulatory messages from
central government departments in which they all spoke highly of
the paper's contributions to deepening mutual understanding and
common prosperity between Hong Kong and the mainland by adhering
to loving the country and loving Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1948, the newspaper is widely circulated over 100
countries and regions in the world. It has set up offices in
nearly 30 cities in the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
Among those present were ann Tse-Kai and Henry Fok Ying-tung,
vice-chairmen of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), Jiang
Enzhu, director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, and Ma
Yuzhen, commissioner of the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs in
the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Also present were Wang Fengchao, deputy director of the Xinhua
News Agency Hong Kong Branch, Anson Chan, administrative secretary
of the HKSAR, and Dr. Tsang Hin chi, standing committee member of
China's National people's Congress. 
</P>
