<HEADLINE> Hundreds of Houses Burn In Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of houses were burned
in Pulogadung, East Jakarta and Cikini, Central Jakarta, in fires
that broke out only four hours apart, according to Antara News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Fire broke out in a residential area in Cikini at about 1:45
a.m. Wednesday. Some 12 fire engines were sent to extinguish the
fire, which nonetheless razed at least 25 houses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, fire swept through a residential area in Pulogadung
at 9:30 p.m. Tuesday after a stove explosion. Some 15 fire engines
were deployed to the scene but it took firefighters several hours
to put out the fire.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported. 
