<HEADLINE> China not Decided over Soccer Side to Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China has not yet made a
final decision on whether to send the young Olympic team or the
national team to play the Bangkok Asian Games in December, a
spokesman of Chinese Football Association (CFA) said here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nan Yong, excutive president of CFA, denied that China has
decided to send its under-23 soccer team to compete in the Asian
Games, which had been widely reported by some home newspapers.
</P>
<P>
"It's just a rumor," said Nan in a rutine news brief of CFA.
"Until this moment, CFA has not decided which team will represent
China to play the Asian Games."
</P>
<P>
However, Nan said it will not take a long time before CFA's
decision comes out.
</P>
<P>
"We are pondering on it seriously," Nan said. "But our
decision has to be approved by the State's General Bureau of
Sports, China's sports governing body."
</P>
<P>
Earlier, national team boss Bob Houghton also said that China
will send its under-23 team to play the Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Football Confederation (AFC) has recommended young
sides compete in the Asiad.
</P>
<P>
Peter Velappan, secretary general of AFC, said in July that
the soccer competition of the Asian Games should be a showcase
for the continent's young talents.
</P>
<P>
South Korea has announced to field its Olympic to the Asian
Games but Japan, another main contenders for the Games, has yet
to make the final decsion, Nan said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
