<HEADLINE> Yap Quits Badminton after Commonwealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's top doubles
player Yap Kim Hock confirmed Wednesday that he will be quitting
after the Commonwealth Games due to injury.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Yap has been suffering from a shoulder injury
for two years.
</P>
<P>
Yap, partnered with Cheah Soon Kit since 1994, has won Olympic
silver, Asian Games gold and a World Grand Prix title.
</P>
<P>
They are also the badminton men's doubles defending champions
at the Commonwealth Games here. 
</P>
