<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Bank Halts Trade Payments to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The bank for foreign trade of
Vietnam has suspended the settlement of import-export payments to
Russian banks at the request of Russian companies, a newspaper
report said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Due to current difficulties in Russian financial institutions,
several Russian firms have asked to freeze trade payments to
Russian banks, a Vietnamese bank official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, no import-export payments for Russian businesses have
fallen due, said the official, adding that the annual trade
payments are just a few million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the foreign trade between the two countries valued
at about 300 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, the Russian central bank suspended the trade on the
electronic system of the Moscow Interbank currency exchange as
demand for the U.S. dollar was exceeding supply, which sent the
ruble plummeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
