<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed higher Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100 quality stocks Composite Index rose 40.09
points to 389.65, the all-share Emas Index increased 8.51 points
to 102.52, the Industrial Index soared 69.90 points to 756.28
while the second board index added 2.23 points to 97.23.
</P>
<P>
Gainers thumped losers by 532 to 130, while 81 counters were
unchanged and 179 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 383.473 million shares worth 608.588
million ringgit (160.154 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's
609.854 million shares valued at 1.042 billion ringgit (274.27
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover dropped to 369.764 million shares worth
587.399 million ringgit (154.578 million U.S. dollars) from
579.552 million shares valued at 991.774 million ringgit (260.993
million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover declined to 13.709 million shares
worth 21.189 million ringgit (5.576 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 30.302 million shares valued at 50.981 million ringgit
(13.416 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market turnover was lower at 708,800 shares worth 2.054
million ringgit (0.54 million U.S. dollars) from Tuesday's 4.616
million shares valued at 5.238 million ringgit (1.378 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 13.918
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
24.002 million shares, construction 53.320 million shares,
trade/services 123.900 million shares, infrastructure 3.077
million shares, finance 67.057 million shares, hotels 913,000
shares, properties 33.386 million shares, plantation 8.371 million
shares, mining 860,400 shares, trusts 103,000 shares, closed/fund
112,000 shares and loans 40.743 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
