<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Silk Road Conference Signs Multilateral Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Participants from 35 countries and 12 international
organizations agreed to establish an intergovernmental commission
-- the secretariat in the Baku-based headquarters.
</P>
<P>
As supplements to the main agreement, four technical
agreements were also signed for interaction among member
countries in the fields of automobile and railway transport,
navigation and customs affairs.
</P>
<P>
The 14 core nations of the conference, including Georgia,
Armenia, Azerbaijan, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan,
Uzbekistan, Ukraine, Moldova and Mongolia, issued Baku
Declaration. It expresses the readiness to develop the transport
corridor of "Europe-Caucasus-Asia".
</P>
<P>
Calling this corridor "the road of future", Azerbaijan's
President Geidar Aliyev expressed confidence that the
multilateral agreement will promote the development of trade,
utilization and transportation of power resources and mutually
beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Russia, however, did not accede to the agreements, saying that
it had not taken part in their discussions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
