<HEADLINE> 64 Fire Cases Occur in Myanmar in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A total of 64 fires broke out
in Myanmar in July, killing three people and three cattle and
injuring one people, the official evening paper the City News
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The fires destroyed 237 houses, leaving 1,050 people homeless.
</P>
<P>
Of the fire cases, 85.94 percent were caused by negligence, the
 report said.
</P>
<P>
The authorities have been taking precautionary measures to
prevent the outbreak of fires during the rainy season which began
in June.
</P>
<P>
As Myanmar is situated in the dry zone, many fire cases occur
every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
