<HEADLINE> Egypt Urges Israel to Accept U.S. Initiative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Egypt Wednesday urged Israel to
accept the proposal made by the United States calling for further
Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank in a bid to advance the
peace talks with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinians have accepted the American initiative
unequivocally without any conditions. (But) Israel has not done
so...," Egyptian presidential advisor Osama el-Baz told Xinhua
before a meeting between President Hosni Mubarak and Israeli envoy
Danny Naveh.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has reportedly proposed that Israel withdraw from
another 13.1 percent of the West Bank in a move to salvage the
stalled peace process.
</P>
<P>
El-Baz criticized Israel for setting new conditions on
accepting the proposal by suggesting that 3 percent of the areas
be changed into "nature reserves" where the Palestinians have
limited powers.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that "it is for the Palestinian jurisdiction
and authority to decide without any pressure from any other side"
whether to agree to the Israeli suggestion.
</P>
<P>
Naveh, Israeli cabinet secretary, who arrived here early in the
day, will brief Mubarak on the results of the latest talks between
the Jewish state and the Palestinians on the overdue Israeli
withdrawal from the West Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
