<HEADLINE> Regulations Protect West Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Provincial People's
Congress Standing Committee in east China's Zhejiang Province
recently adopted regulations to prevent pollution around West
Lake, one of China's most famous scenic sites.
</P>
<P>
Individuals and work units are prohibited from discharging
waste, sewage and other pollutants into the lake. The regulations
strictly prohibit individuals from bathing, doing laundry and
swimming in the lake, with violators subject to specified fines.
</P>
<P>
Pleasure boats plying the lake must be powered by electric
motors or solar energy, and plants likely to cause pollution will
be prohibited along rivers which flow into the lake.
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection departments will monitor the lake's
water quality on a regular basis, and regular dredging will be
required to maintain the minimum depth of lake at 1.5 meters.
</P>
</TEXT>
