<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lower in
Tokyo following sharp rises in previous two trading days Wednesday
as buying encouraged by the sharp rise on Wall Street overnight
failed to overcome selling on investors' anxiety over Japan's
ailing economy.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 157.95 points, or 1.06
percent, from Tuesday's close to end at 14,755.54.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, declined 15.00 points or 1.33 percent to
1,116.01.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to an estimated 417
million shares from Tuesday's 490.99 million shares Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Fuji Bank, whose shares fell to a new low for the year on market
rumors that it could see huge losses from overseas derivatives
trading, was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,341 issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 798 to 354, with 141 issues remaining unchanged.
