<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav Foreign Minister
Zivadin Jovanovic Tuesday condemned the European Union (EU) over
its recent decision to ban the landing of Yugoslav planes in EU
member countries.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic made the remarks here while meeting with visiting
Belgian Foreign Minister Eric Derycke, Yugoslav news agency Tanjug
reported.
</P>
<P>
The EU decision is a new and unacceptable discrimination, which
has crudely violated bilateral agreements and international air
transport accords.
</P>
<P>
The decision, which is illegal and has no appropriate political
reasons, is aimed at harming Yugoslav air companies and citizens,
Jovanovic said.
</P>
<P>
