<HEADLINE> Children Back to School on Time Despite Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- All 915 primary and high
schools in the flood-stricken areas of Chongqing, the municipality
at the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, have opened their new
semester on time despite severe flood damage.
</P>
<P>
Floods, mud slides and rock flow have destroyed nearly
40,000-square meters of school space, affecting over 200,000
students and inflicting economic losses of more than 30 million
yuan (about 3.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has allocated 10 million yuan (about
1.3 million U.S. dollars) to restore educational facilities, and
46 schools which have been seriously affected opened the new
semester in tents and leased residential quarters. 
</P>
