<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region will host an eight-day trade fair from December
10-17 to mark the 40th anniversary of the founding of the
autonomous region on December 11.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, to be held in Nanning, the regional capital,
the regional government will issue a list in detail of over 1,000
selected projects in an effort to attract overseas investment and
economic cooperation, said Zhang Wenxue, vice-chairman of the
region, at a recent news conference.
</P>
<P>
 The trade fair will provide 804 exhibit booths where
delegates will conduct negotiations, commodity exhibitions and
trading, displays of scientific and technological achievements,
and transactions of property rights.
</P>
<P>
The region has been busy preparing for the fair, said the vice
chairman, adding that some provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions have agreed to organize delegations to attend
the event.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi charged up to third place in China in foreign trade
growth in 1997, and also placed higher in the use of overseas
investment and in gross domestic product growth (GDP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
