<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Incoming Overseas Investment up in Ningxia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
in northwest China now obtains one-fourth of its construction
financing from overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that direct overseas investment in
Ningxia--home of the Chinese Muslims-- has topped 300 million
U.S. dollars, with foreign aids amounting to 170 million
U.S. dollars and foreign loans exceeding 200 million
U.S. dollars. The region has gained investors from 26 countries
and regions around the world.
</P>
<P>
Though the amount of overseas investment is relatively small in
comparison with coastal regions, inland Ningxia has managed to use
its money efficiently, said an official of the foreign trade and
cooperation office.
</P>
<P>
The local government has already made effort to attract
overseas money to the area of infrastructure construction badly in
need of improvement, and to pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
For example, foreign funds have been used for airport
construction, trans-regional natural gas pipelines, agriculture,
water conservancy, and for improving rural telephone facilities.
</P>
<P>
With the help of investment from Singapore, the Yinchuan Rubber
Factory has developed eighteen new products to become the third
largest rubber-tire producer in China.
</P>
<P>
Under preferential policies announced by the government,
overseas investors can invest in shares or participate in
enterprise mergers and acquisition, and enjoy tax breaks in
Ningxia.
</P>
<P>
Efforts have also been made to improve investment
management. For example, all of the 28 completed projects
involving foreign loans were carried out under a system of strict
supervision.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over 60 percent of all overseas-funded
projects have been successful.  
</P>
</TEXT>
