<HEADLINE> CAST set to Donate Books to Flood-Stricken Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The China Association for
Science and Technology (CAST) today commissioned a group of flood
control, disease prevention and agricultural specialists to
compile a set of books which will be distributed in flood-stricken
areas.
</P>
<P>
The books, which will be compiled by experts from the State
Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters, Chinese Academy of
Agriculture and Jishuitan Hospital, will teach residents in the
flood-stricken areas methods to prevent the spread of infectious
diseases, pink eye and various other epidemic diseases, as well as
approaches for resuming agricultural and husbandry production at
the earliest possible date.
</P>
<P>
Over 250,000 books valued at over one million yuan (120,000 US
dollars) will mainly be distributed in Anhui and Hubei provinces,
according to one CAST official.
</P>
<P>
He added that CAST, a national organization of Chinese
scientists and technologists, has called on scientists working in
the scientific and technological institutions throughout the
nation to help local health departments prevent and control
diseases and advise local governments on the construction of water
conservancy failities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
