<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Gov't, Opposition to Unite in Facing Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The ruling party and the
opposition of Bangladesh have reached an agreement to work
together to mitigate the sufferings of the flood-affected people.
</P>
<P>
The two sides arrived at a consensus Tuesday following a
four-and- half-hour general discussion in the parliament on the
country's nearly two-month-long devastating flood, press reports
here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, chairperson of the ruling Awami
League, and Khaleda Zia, chairperson of the opposition, the
Nationalist Party of Bangladesh, made identical calls for standing
by the side of the people at this hour of disaster.
</P>
<P>
The discussion was attended by as many as 37 lawmakers from the
opposition and treasury benches.
</P>
<P>
However, the reports did not elaborate on how the agreement
would be implemented.
</P>
<P>
The opposition had repeatedly accused the government of
mismanaging relief supplies and called for setting up an all-party
flood relief committee on several occasions, but the government
declined. 
</P>
