<HEADLINE> Thailand to Give More Funding to Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 9 (Xinhua) -- An urgent working plan worth
200 million U.S. dollars will be introduced to develop Thailand's
agricultural sector, a government press release available
Wednesday said.
</P>
<P>
Half of the 200 million dollars will be allocated for the
quality development and management of agricultural products in
order to deliver the products to consumers and export markets.
</P>
<P>
The credit will fund the operation of seven agricultural
product centers which will be run by a farmer institution or the
private sector.
</P>
<P>
About 85 million dollars will be allocated for the promotion
of an alternative agricultural system, which aims to boost
short-term production of plants, livestock and fishery and
processing of the products.
</P>
<P>
The rest 15 million dollars will go to communities for
forestry rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, another 400 million dollars
will be allocated for a medium working plan to improve production
efficiency in the irrigation zone and establish a special
export-oriented economic zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
