<HEADLINE>   Vietnam Deplores Violent Actions in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 8 (xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government
Tuesday expressed indignation at the violent actions against
ethnic vietnamese in cambodia.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Foreign Ministry said a number of
extremist elements in Cambodia, driven by "political conflicts",
have led to terrorist acts and killing of ethnic vietnamese.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government and people "vehemently protest these
barbarous acts taken by a number of extremists which seriously
violate human rights and further complicate the situation in
Cambodia", the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam urges King Sihanouk, with his prestige and influence,
to prevent the recurrence of "such racialist crimes against
Vietnamese".
</P>
<P>
The statement also called on the Cambodian government to take
immediate and strong actions to stop the violent acts and ensure
the safety and property of the ethnic Vietnamese in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam warmly welcomes the success of the general election in
Cambodia, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam hopes a new government will be established early in
Cambodia to stabilize the situation, thus contributing to the
stability in Southeast Asia, the statement said. 
</P>
