<HEADLINE> Mexico's Economy to Grow 4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The prospect of Mexico's
economic growth will be close to 4 percent in the next two years,
Public Finance Minister Jose Angel Gurria Trevino said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Gurria said the growth rate he projected is lower than that of
the National Financing for Development Program, mainly because of
the international financial crisis and lower oil prices.
</P>
<P>
According to Gurria, the Mexican authorities will adjust
public financing so that it would not be necessary to contract
further debts to achieve balance between national revenues and
spending.
</P>
<P>
"We are reacting cautiously and prudently in the face of events
over which we can't control, but there is a possibility to adjust
things to prevent imbalance," Gurria said. 
