<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Passes New Measures to Boost Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Tuesday
acknowledged a resolution of the Economic Ministers' Council
meeting to introduce new measures in the second half of 1998 to
boost export-oriented investment, a government press release said.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Ministers' Council meeting held on Monday decided
that imported machinery tax in some areas and raw material tax for
export-oriented investment, especially in leather products and
garments, will be exempted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, tax burden on over-five-year-old machinery will be
cut off more rapidly and the transfer of less-than-5-year-old
machinery will not be taxed, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The council also decided to help small-scaled local investors
who are facing liquidity problems by matching them with foreign
partners.
</P>
<P>
The Board of Investment will serve as an information center and
market for foreign purchasers and local sellers.
</P>
<P>
The council hoped this measure will induce the flow-in of
foreign capital and also support technology transfer to the Thai
industry. 
</P>
