<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Produce Quality Pearls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is striving to produce
more than 375 kilograms of quality pearls in five years with an
annual output of 75 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Research is being made on oyster breeding and pearl culture
systematically and means are also being sought to reduce their
mortality rate, the official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pearls are widely cultured in Southern Tanintharyi division of
Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Since March last year, three companies from Japan, Australia
and Thailand respectively have reached contracts with the
state-run Myanmar Pearl Enterprise to culture pearls at islands in
the division.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar's cultured pearl
production in the 1997-98 fiscal year, which ended in March,
reached 28.41 kilograms while its highest record was 66.9
kilograms in the 1983-84 fiscal year. 
</P>
