<HEADLINE> Italian President Puts Off Visit to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The scheduled state visit by
Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro to Russia on Sunday will be
postponed, announced the president's office in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The postponement is agreed by both sides and a new date
will be decided soon, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Russia is now experiencing a serious economic and political
turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin planned to bring Viktor
Chernomyrdin back to the post of prime minister to save the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
However, Russia's State Duma, or the lower house of parliament,
overwhelmingly rejected Chernomyrdin as prime minister for the
second time on Monday and is very likely to reject him again in
the third and final round of voting if Yeltsin insists on
nominating Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin invited Scalfaro during his own state visit to Italy in
February.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro's three-day state visit would have been the first to
Russia by a head of state since that of U.S. President Bill
Clinton earlier this month. 
</P>
