<HEADLINE> North China Province Encourages Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The number of private
businesses in north China's Hebei Province has grown to 325,000 so
far this year.
</P>
<P>
Their business scope has expanded from commerce and service
trades to 250 types of industry in eight categories including
building. transportation, real estate, scientific consultancy,
medicine and education.
</P>
<P>
They employed a total workforce of 12,000, and over 300 firms
have registered capital of more than one million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
To date, 200 such firms are engaged in scientific research and
development, and more than 500 have exported their products around
the world.
</P>
<P>
The government of Shijiazhuang, the provincial capital,
recently issued a policy to encourage the development of private
businesses through merging with the state sector and expansion of
production scale. The policy also specifies measures that favor
the flow of capitals, human resources and land property rights to
the private sector. 
</P>
