<HEADLINE> Johansson Upset Kafelnikov at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Unfancied Sweden's Thomas
Johansson upset No. 11 Yevgeny Kafelnikov of 3-6, 6-3, 6-3, 7-6
8-6) to gain his first ever berth in the quarterfinals of the
U.S. Open tennis championships here today.
</P>
<P>
Johansson's victory, his second straight over a seeded player,
registered the 23-year-old best appearance in a Grand Slam
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Johansson took advantage by keeping the ball down the middle
to cut the angle and letting Kafelnikov self-destruct by pounding
groundstrokes into the net or spraying them around the court.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov appeared to get back in the match in the fourth set
when he took a 4-1 lead. But, beginning with the third point of
the sixth game, the Swede ran off 11 straight points to knot the
set at 4-all.
</P>
<P>
Johansson reached his first match point at 30-40 in the 10th
game before Kafelnikov captured the next three points to level
the set at 5-5.
</P>
<P>
In the tiebreak, Johansson jumped out to a 5-2 lead. Again
Kafelnikov rallied back, but on the third match point, Johansson
finally closed out the win when he rifled a backhand down the
line.
</P>
<P>
Johansson has been lucky at the Open. He reached the fourth
round when No.5 Richard Krajicek retired with tendinitis of the
knee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
