<HEADLINE> Rafter Beats Ivanisevic at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion and third
seed Patrick Rafter of Australia continued to look strong as he
completed a 6-3, 6-4, 4-6, 6-1 triumph over 14th seed Goran
Ivanisevic of Croatia here today at the U.S. Open tennis champions
hips.
</P>
<P>
Nine men's seeds and four women's seeds were scheduled as the
day's schedule was crowded by Monday's postponements. Rafter
broke at love to take a commanding two-set lead, Ivanisevic went
up a break in the ninth game of the third set and served it out.
</P>
<P>
But Rafter continually frustrated Ivanisevic in the fourth
set,causing the Croatian to fling his racket, which just missed a
ballboy. Rafter broke Ivanisevic in the second game and again in
the sixth before grabbing the match.
</P>
<P>
Rafter was successful on 75 percent of his first serves, broke
Ivanisevic five times and won 110 points to Ivanisevic's
87.Meanwhile Ivanisevic landed only 40 percent of his first
serves and committed 26 unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
"He wasn't making mistakes at all and I just had to win a
couple of points to get my confidence back," said Kucera, who
capitalized on the fifth break point.
</P>
<P>
Rafter will face number 12 Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden in the
quarterfinals. Bjorkman, a semifinalist last year, closed out a
6-4, 2-6, 6-2, 6-2 victory over Dutchman Jan Siemerink.
</P>
<P>
This afternoon, 33rd-ranked Thomas Johansson of Sweden
advanced to his first Grand Slam quarterfinals when he beat 11th
seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia 3-6, 6-3, 6-3, 7-6 (8-6).
</P>
<P>
There are just two women's matches today, but all four players
are seeded. Third seed Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic beat
No.11 Patty Schnyder 6-2, 6-3. Schnyder knocked off five-time
U.S. Open champion Steffi Graf of Germany on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
Martina Hingis of Switzerland has to be on top of her game
when she faces two-time champion Monica Seles of the United
States in the quarterfinal tonight. Hingis won all five meetings
with Seles last year, but has dropped both matches this year.In
their most recent meeting, Seles rallied for a three-set win in
the semifinals of an international tournament three weeks ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
