<HEADLINE> Leeds United Leads English Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- An overwhelming victory over
Southampton propelled Leeds United to the top of the English
Premier League on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In its fourth match of the season, Leeds blanked Southampton
3-0 at Elland Road.
</P>
<P>
An own goal by Scott Marshall seven minutes before the break
set the tone and Leeds's Ian Harte doubled the hosts' lead seven
minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
George Graham's side dominated the match from start to finish
against a Southampton side that looked to have few ideas and
Dutch summer signing Clyde Wijnhard scored the third goal minutes
from the end.
</P>
<P>
The victory sees Leeds go top -- a point above Liverpool who
entertain Coventry on Wednesday -- while Southampton stay rooted
at the bottom of the table, still without a point.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's other match, Everton scored their first goals of
the season as they beat Nottingham Forest 2-0 away.
</P>
<P>
Two goals from Scottish center forward Duncan Ferguson
finished off Forest who, had they won, would have gone top of the
league.
</P>
<P>
Ferguson broke the stalemate with a trademark header in the
72nd minute and finished matters six minutes from time with a
left foot shot from the edge of the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
