<DOCNO> XIE19980909.0294 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Merson Completes Transfer to Aston Villa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Paul Merson completed his 6.75
million pounds (11.28 million U.S. dollars) transfer to Aston
Villa on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said after the transfer that his decision to leave
Middlesbrough had nothing to do with Paul Gascoigne.
</P>
<P>
"Gazza is one of my closest friends," said the 30 year-old
England international after agreeing a deal that will keep him at
Villa Park for the rest of this season and the following three
years.
</P>
<P>
But Merson admitted: "There were problems behind the scenes at
Middlesbrough that I am not prepared to talk about.
</P>
<P>
"Things have got a bit out of hand over the last week because
I was stitched up by someone I thought was a friend who has made
money out of all this.
</P>
<P>
"Otherwise I would have sorted everything out amicably with
Bryan Robson. He understands my problem, and would have let me
go. I can't speak highly enough of him."
</P>
<P>
But Merson acknowledged his concerns went "much deeper" than
the fear of being lured back into "booze and betting" which
almost destroyed his career at Arsenal.
</P>
<P>
"The last year or so has been a roller coaster time for me and
I basically needed some stability, which I believe I will get at
Villa," he added.
</P>
<P>
But his signing was not completed in time to make his debut in
Wednesday night's premier league game with Newcastle at Villa
Park.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the league's registration's department said:
"The transfer missed the noon deadline by about three hours."
</P>
<P>
Villa manager John Gregory believes Merson's arrival will have
the same affect on Villa as Eric Cantona's did on Manchester
United.
</P>
<P>
"He is that important a signing to me," said Gregory. "I know
for certain that everyone in our dressing room will look up to
Paul Merson.
</P>
<P>
"A lot of people wrote him off when he left Arsenal for
Middlesbrough. But he has overcome all his problems and is now
playing as well as ever again, as his selection for the England
team in Sweden proves.
</P>
<P>
"I admire him for the way he has put his life and career back
together. It takes a strong man to do that the way he has.
</P>
<P>
"He was Boro's outstanding player last season and I have no
doubts he is going to be a major asset for us."
</P>
<P>
Merson revealed Boro had tried to persuade him to return to
London to join Tottenham instead of moving to the Midlands.
</P>
<P>
"They might have had it mind to swap me for one of Spurs'
players," he said.
</P>
<P>
"But I played for Arsenal for 13 years which is a good enough
reason for not joining Tottenham.
</P>
<P>
"Villa are a massive club who are going places, with a great
manager who has done unbelievable. So everything about the move
is right for me." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
