<HEADLINE> World Cup Coaches' Victim Toll Reaches 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 21 coaches have
resigned since the World Cup in France after Germany's Berti
Vogts and Buglaria's Hristo Bonev left their posts this week.
</P>
<P>
Following is a list of the departures since the start of the
World Cup tournament, which ran from June 10 to July 12
(replacements to be announced unless stated):
