<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce's Orders Show UK Aerospace's Strength </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Rolls-Royce plc, a
global aerospace company, announced a total of 1.5 billion U.S.
dollars worth of orders at the on-going Farnborough Air Show
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The orders were for Trent 500 and the AE3007 engines, according
to a news release made available to the press at Farnborough,
southwest of London. The Trent 500 is the only engine available
for the Airbus Industrie A340-500/600.
</P>
<P>
Also, orders and options for up to 26 aircraft were announced
Tuesday from the Emirates, the Dubai-based airline, and
International Lease Finance Corporation.
</P>
<P>
That brings the total order book for Trent 500 to nearly 5
billion U.S. dollars. In addition, six aerospace companies from
the United States, the United Kingdom, Italy, Spain and Japan
Tuesday took a 24 percent state in the program.
</P>
<P>
John Rose, Rolls-Royce chief executive and president of the
Society of British Aerospace Companies, said at Farnborough,
"Today's orders reflect the strength of the breadth of our product
range and the advantage we have in being the sole engine supplier
for 17 of our 32 civil aircraft applications. It also demonstrates
the strength of the UK aerospace industry." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
