<HEADLINE> U.S. Denies Seizure of Iraqi Vessel in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The United States on
Tuesday denied a report that the U.S. military had detained an
Iraqi vessel in the Gulf which was carrying grain bought under
an "oil-for-food" agreement with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
"Over the past weekend, 11 vessels were boarded (in the Gulf
region) and were cleared. None were detained," Pentagon spokesman
Marine Lt. Col. Pat Sivigny said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's news agency INA has said that according to an Iraqi
Trade Ministry source, the vessel had been taken into custody
inside Iraqi territorial waters on Sunday and the U.S. forces
were responsible for the safety of the vessel and the crew.
</P>
</TEXT>
