<HEADLINE> Chinese Lawmaker Tables Out Task </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A ranking Chinese legislator
Tuesday urged the world community to rectify erroneous tendencies
in the international human rights field and chart a clear course
for future efforts.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Jianhui, chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress, told the on-going 100th
Conference of the Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) in the Kremlin
that efforts should be made to earnestly review the experience and
lessons of the past 50 years since the birth of the Universal
Declaration of Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
"Review the past and you will know better the present," Zeng
said by quoting an old Chinese saying.
</P>
<P>
He urged the North and the South to end confrontation and
strengthen cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zeng also called for rectification of the tendency of placing
civil and political rights ahead of economic, social and cultural
rights and the right to development.
</P>
<P>
"Equal importance shall be attached to all these rights, paying
earnest attention to the needs of the people of developing
countries and taking concrete measures to help these countries out
of poverty and attain development so as to create conditions for
them to fully enjoy all human rights," Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
When handling human rights issues, Zeng said, the international
community should, first and foremost, address the cases involving
massive and gross violations of human rights triggered by all
forms of racism, colonialism and hegemonism and remove the
impediments to the materialization of economic, social and
cultural rights in developing countries caused by the inequitable
international economic order.
</P>
<P>
In his opinion, another major task facing the international
community in the field of human rights is to rectify the tendency
of politicizing and ideologizing human rights and obtain a correct
understanding of the relationship between the universality and
particularity of human rights.
</P>
<P>
"It is the common ideal and objective of mankind to achieve
universal human rights, and human rights should be practiced and
realized in light of the actual conditions of each country," Zeng
said at the meeting, held on the 50th anniversary of the Universal
Declaration of Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
"Given their differences in historical, cultural, economic and
political development, countries are bound to achieve human rights
in different ways," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the world community to "recognize the disparity and
particularity of the conditions of various countries, respect the
choice of their people regarding the roads to development and be
fully affirmative and supportive of the efforts by all countries,
the vast number of developing countries in particular, in the
promotion and protection of human rights."
</P>
<P>
"It will only give rise to confrontations to regard the human
rights model and policy of one's own country as universal and
impose them on others, to interfere in the internal affairs of
other countries under the pretext of the universality principle of
human rights and even to resort to sanctions or threat of
sanctions against other countries," Zeng warned.
</P>
<P>
He called on the world community to redouble its efforts at the
international and national levels, in the spirit of mutual respect
and unity, to build a world in which people all over the world
will be able to fully enjoy human rights and democracy and achieve
development and common prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
