<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 181 Countries to Take Part in GA General Debate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jin Yongjian, under-secretary-general for General Assembly
affairs and conference services, told a press conference that 26
heads of state and 20 heads of government will take the floor in
the general debate, which is scheduled for September 21.
</P>
<P>
The Uruaguan foreign minister was elected president of the
General Assembly, and the General Committee will meet on Friday to
discuss and decide on 169 items on the draft agenda, Jin said.
</P>
<P>
The items include peace and security, the social and economic
impact of the globalization, the conflicts in Africa, and
sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
The 53rd session of the General Assembly will kick off on
Wednesday, about one week earlier than usual. The General
Assembly's regular session used to begin each year on the third
Tuesday of September and continue until mid-December.
</P>
<P>
The 52nd session of the General Assembly concluded on Tuesday
after a year of extensive discussion on 163 items.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly, the main deliberative organ under the
United Nations, is composed of representatives of all 185 member
states, each of which has one vote.
</P>
<P>
Security has been beefed up this week in the complex of the
U.N. headquarters in preparation for the upcoming session of the
General Assembly, U.N. security sources told Xinhua on Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
