<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Warns of Possible Conflict With Cameroon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian Defense
Headquarters has warned of a possible military confrontation at
the oil-rich Bakassi Peninsula, which was both claimed by Nigeria
and Cameroon.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Headquarters said in a statement Tuesday in Lagos
that authorities in Yaounde last week deployed more troops to the
disputed areas along its border with Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
It noted, however, it was not clear if the Cameroonians had
deployed heavy weapons to back the deployed troops.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Nigeria believes that there should be no
confrontation to escalate the tension there and that it will
stick to the judgement of the International Court of Justice
(ICJ).
</P>
<P>
It said that Nigeria plans "to maintain a peaceful stance in
conformity with the ICJ, and we do hope that Cameroon would
follow suit, but we are there watching their action."
</P>
<P>
Nigeria and Cameroon have clashed for several times in the
last few years at Bakassi, a peninsula in the Guinea Gulf in West
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The dispute have been filed to the ICJ but the judgement is
being expected.  
</P>
</TEXT>
