<HEADLINE> UNDP Launches Community Development Trust Fund in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) has created a new trust fund in
Indonesia to collect and target donor contributions for the
country's Community Recovery Program, a release from UNDP said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
As a result of Indonesia's severe economic crisis, there is a
strong need for funding and community development projects for
poor communities, with special emphasis on women and children.
</P>
<P>
The aid provided through the fund is being channeled to
community organizations and to local projects that support
income-generating activities, small enterprises and education and
health services for rural children and women.
</P>
<P>
The United Kingdom made an initial pledge to the fund last
week, and the UNDP has announced it will provide 500,000 U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
