<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- European stock markets closed
mixed on Tuesday, with London remaining basically unchanged while
Frankfurt and Paris soaring ahead inspired by Wall Street's strong
opening.
</P>
<P>
Shares on the London stock market had a subdued day despite the
surge which swept through Wall Street this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Despite a flood of good results from several FTSE 100
companies, the index wobbled throughout the day. At one stage, it
peaked up 52.8 at 5,399.8.
</P>
<P>
Even a dramatic rise on Wall Street during the afternoon failed
to stir the FTSE 100 Index which ended the day down 2.8 points at
5,344.2.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, share prices on the Frankfurt stock exchange
rocketed ahead, hyped up by Wall Street's strength in the first
part of the New York session.
</P>
<P>
The Dax index gained a hefty 3.67 percent on the day to finish
at 5,103.84 points, against 4,923.37 at the end of trading on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Traders noted that Wall Street was up almost 4 percent in the
first half-hour. But Frankfurt operators remained cautious.
</P>
<P>
One trader said: "In the short term, we are going to continue
to see high volatility, as long as things in Russia are up in the
air."
</P>
<P>
In Paris, share prices closed sharply higher in heavy trade as
Wall Street's strong opening and merger speculation in the banking
sector sparked a wave of buying.
</P>
<P>
The Cac 40 index finished 108.39 points, or 2.9 percent, higher
at 3,803.74. After a relatively flat morning, the index shot
higher in the afternoon, spurred by Wall Street's initial rally.
</P>
<P>
"Basically we were in line with the rest of Europe, and people
had been expecting Wall Street to open higher all day," said one
dealer.
</P>
<P>
Worries about the international picture were temporarily eased
by gains made in Asian markets overnight.
</P>
<P>
"The markets have been oversold, it's been good overnight in
Asia and there's still money to be invested," the dealer added.
</P>
</TEXT>
